Some of the week\'92s developments point forward. Courts are now seized with the administration\'92s emergency appeal to terminate diversity-related grants, and with lawsuits over frozen education funds and new funding conditions on HUD and HHS programs. Judge Engelmayer in New York has set deadlines for DOJ, Maxwell, and Epstein victims to brief the request to unseal Maxwell grand jury materials, with filings due in late July and early August. The House Oversight Committee has subpoenaed Maxwell for an August deposition and plans to subpoena DOJ for the Epstein files, setting up a confrontation over executive privilege and grand jury secrecy. Senators Graham and Cornyn have called for a special counsel to investigate Obama-era intelligence assessments, which would further entrench the narrative of a \'93treasonous conspiracy\'94 if granted. On the technology front, agencies have 120 days to implement the \'93Preventing Woke AI\'94 order, and the Commerce Department will soon solicit proposals for the American AI Exports Program, decisions that will shape the AI ecosystem for years.\
